The National Assembly has approved the appointment of five nominees as members of the Teachers Service Commission (TSC). The five are now set to be sworn in after being nominated by President Uhuru Kenyatta on August 12, 2021 and given the all-clear by the House on Wednesday. The five; Dr. Nicodemus Ojuma Anyang, Christine K. Kahindi, Sharon Jelagat Kisire, Annceta G. Wafukho, and Salesa Adano Abudo, were nominated upon the Presidentâ€™s receipt of the report of the Selection Panel. President Kenyatta then forwarded the names to the National Assembly for approval in accordance with the Teachers Service Commission Act No.20 of 2012. The National Assembly, according to the Act, had 21 days to consider each of the nominations and approve or reject them. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis